name: Brady Leman

social_posts.post_text: Just like that, another growing season comes to a tragic close. I’d love to keep my lip sweater a bit longer, but it’s scientifically proven that my stache is fast in #movember but not so much in December 🥹. Thanks to everyone who donated to my @movember campaign, over $500 raised!! And for those who want their donations to stay local, please check out the @prostatecancercentre as a great spot to support mens health right at home in AB!

Disappointing couple days of racing for me in @val_thorens. Started off hot with back to back quali wins but a few mistakes in the heats meant I was out early both days. Lots more racing to come this month and I know I’m skiing fast so I know there’s better results coming! 
•
@lululemon @skilouise @elanskis @canfund @oakleyskiing #alwaysgoodtimes #lululemonambassador #prairieskyroyalties  #canfundrecipient 
•
First photo GEPA/ @alpinecanada, photos 2&3 @tetsuyafuruno 🤘🏼
Few snaps from the last few weeks 🤙🏼🦈❤️🏝️🏄‍♀️⛷️🚡#thriving. Up in 🇸🇪 now are ready to fire it back up this weekend

Always a treat to get a few days skiing at home at @skilouise! Stress free ski days are rare for me, and I love whenever I get a change to rip around my favourite hill in the world. I’ve been lucky to be supported by Charlie and his team at Lake Louise for basically my whole career and after growing up skiing here it’s still my favourite place in the world to spend a day on the hill. Headed back over to Europe today to prepare for the final push of this World Cup season! #JustLakeIt #LakeLouise #Banff #Alberta #Canada 📸: @travisnrousseau
Obrigadddoooooo 🇵🇹

Lots of emotions with this post 🥹🥹. Those close to me have known this for a while…this weekends Ski Cross World Cup & World Cup finals in Craigleith, Ontario will be my last as I’ve decided to retire at the end of the season. 
•
It’s been a truly amazing ride, I’ve accomplished some of my wildest dreams, and 10 year old Brady is so happy and proud.
•
So many emotions come up with this, but the main one is gratitude. Thank you ski racing, thank you to my family, friends, teammates, staff, sponsors, competitors and everyone who has been a part of this journey. It’s truly been a dream come true. 
•
No victory lap for this guy, I’ll be racing hard right until the end and trying to end my career with a W!!
•
Leaving on my terms, in one piece with a smile on my face and maybe a few tears, stay tuned for more but for now…
•
#THANKYOUSKIRACING

When you ask @lemanracing to ONLY pick 5 top moments of his career 🤯. Brady has been in the game since the beginning with @canadaskicross and we will miss hearing his name announced in the gate. His dedication and passion is unmatched, as is his extensive resume 😅 (Gold Olympic Medal, Gold X Games Medal, Silver World Championship Medal, 31 World Cup podiums.. to name a few). Is this fake news? Ask him yourself at Craigleith this weekend! 🐐 

🔗 Link in bio.
-
Quand on demande à @lemanracing de choisir SEULEMENT 5 moments forts de sa carrière 🤯. Brady a été un athlète à surveiller depuis ses débuts avec @canadaskicross et l’annonce de son nom dans le portillon de départ va nous manquer. Sa passion et son dévouement sont inégalés, tout comme son long CV 😅 (médaille d’or olympique, médaille d’or aux X Games, médaille d’argent aux Mondiaux, 31 podiums en Coupe du monde... pour ne nommer que quelques-uns de ses exploits). Est-ce vraiment une fausse nouvelle? Venez lui poser la question vous-même à Craigleith ce week-end! 🐐

People keep asking me what’s next now that I’m retired from ski racing…full time stay at home dog dad to @the_goldenboycharlie

Retirement is a weird time. Some days I ride the couch, some days I do a bunch of housework, and apparently some days I throw on some hip hop and do a 1,000 lb challenge in the garage for no reason. Extra spice with 3 reps. RIP legs 🪦💀 also, clearly since all these ski legs are good for now is holding up my pants I better get my bench up! (Squat 385, DL 405, bench 225 😢, total 1,015lbs)

Hear @lemanracing talk about his love of skiing, his experiences and the people who’ve supported him on his journey. 🥲🤘

We will miss Brady racing for Canada, but we look forward to seeing him continue to rip up the slopes and rock his cowboy hat. #GOAT 🤠 🐐 
-

Brady nous manquera dans les courses pour représenter le Canada, mais nous avons hâte de le voir continuer à dévaler les pentes et à brandir son chapeau de cow-boy. #GOAT 🤠🐐
